<subSubSection pageId="5" pageNumber="28" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="5.[264,1325,284,870]" pageId="5" pageNumber="28">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[312,433,644,670]" pageId="5" pageNumber="28">Remarks.</emphasis>
This species was originally described with specimens from “ 
<collectingCountry box="[1167,1305,644,670]" name="Costa Rica" pageId="5" pageNumber="28">Costa Rica</collectingCountry>
;” Volcán de Irazú, Cache, 
<collectingCountry box="[559,693,684,710]" name="Costa Rica" pageId="5" pageNumber="28">Costa Rica</collectingCountry>
; Bugaba, 
<collectingCountry box="[814,910,684,710]" name="Panama" pageId="5" pageNumber="28">Panama</collectingCountry>
; and 
<collectingRegion box="[976,1096,684,710]" country="Nicaragua" name="Chontales" pageId="5" pageNumber="28">Chontales</collectingRegion>
, 
<collectingCountry box="[1110,1234,684,710]" name="Nicaragua" pageId="5" pageNumber="28">Nicaragua</collectingCountry>
. Bates noted the variation of large body size (
<quantity box="[712,795,724,750]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.1" pageId="5" pageNumber="28" unit="mm" value="11.0">11 mm</quantity>
) and dark color of the middle and hind tibiae in the specimens from 
<collectingRegion box="[544,665,764,790]" country="Nicaragua" name="Chontales" pageId="5" pageNumber="28">Chontales</collectingRegion>
. Worn specimens are difficult to identify without the examination of male genitalia, because the distribution of setae on the elytra is an important diagnostic character.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
